<Paintings>
  <Text -120 -130 12 #000000 0 "based on: https://electronics.stackexchange.com/questions/121670/zener-mosfet-overvoltage-protection\ntriple P-mosfet circuit\n5.1Vz goes from 4.98V-5.2V; results in 5.05V-5.53V\n5.68Vz is 5.49V-5.7V; results in 5.75V-5.78V\nboth with ngspice; Xyce results in 6V for 5.6Vz!!\nXyze 5.8V-6.02V (5.6Vz), 5.33V-5.53V (5.1Vz)\nThe version with a PNP BJT behaves nicer in Xyze & Ngspice... (stackexchange2.sch)">
</Paintings>
